The Dragonfly Reset Loop (DRL v1.0)

Use this whenever pattern recognition feels “electric.”

Step 1 — Spark (Dragonfly Active)

You notice:
	•	Convergence
	•	Symbol repetition
	•	Cross-domain echo
	•	“This fits too well”

Pause.

⸻

Step 2 — Freeze Frame (Sommelier Engages)

Ask:
	1.	What is raw observation?
	2.	What is interpretation?
	3.	What is extrapolation?

Separate all three.

Most pattern inflation occurs here.

⸻

Step 3 — Null Model Test

What is the boring explanation?
	•	Random clustering?
	•	Confirmation bias?
	•	Selection effect?
	•	Base rate?

If the null model survives, Dragonfly stands down.

If the pattern still holds after null pressure, continue.

⸻

Step 4 — Projection Cone (Dragonfly Returns)

Instead of:
“This must be true”

Ask:
“If this pattern is real, what measurable prediction follows?”

Attach time window + falsifiable marker.

No prediction = aesthetic pattern only.

⸻

Step 5 — Containment

Log it.
Don’t marry it.
Let it earn survival through time.

Patterns that persist across contexts without reinforcement are strong.

⸻

